How to choose mattress and somier: women and men seek different things
Nothing about a pompous bed frame; what really gives its quality to a good bed is the surface to lie down, i.e. the mattress and the somier.
First and foremost, they must be complemented perfectly so that they are adapted to specific users.
During the election numerous elements come into play, including the owner's weight, height, health status and sex.
It is also important the type of interior in which the mattress and somier are located.
A typical example?
For example, in a weekend cottage that does not usually have heating, latex mattresses should not be used because they "heat" more slowly.
In addition, they often weigh considerably more than the usual polyurethane mattresses.
It is therefore necessary to turn them around more often.
If the canals of the center are not properly aired and above, they are on a firm basis, keep the moisture inside. Even mold may appear below.
When choosing a bed, customs are also influenced.
Anyone who has spent a lot of time abroad often uses a very high mattress with a soft layer and will have trouble feeling well on a lower and harder surface.
"Almost all the hockey players who came back from NHL complained that they didn't sleep as well here."
"For their wrecked shoulders, heels and hips they needed mattresses with a soft layer of viscoelastics."
"This type of mattress is also recommended for people with diabetes who have time problems with the nervous system, so they get poor information from the joints and skin," explains Sylva Hadamcziková, who specializes in padded furniture.
Many hockey players, like other customers, have long preferred viscoelastic mattresses.
"Today there is no problem, because they have these suitable Tempur and the Italian Magnifles, but also the Czech brand Tropico."
You don't have to be a player of the NHL anymore to appreciate the viscoelastics.
This "miracle" works in a very simple way.
Optimizes its rigidity and shape depending on the absorbed heat or adapts to its body heat.
Nothing exerts pressure; during the night, it will not turn around like after a hard game.
She just sleeps better.
Viscoelastic also works as protection against wounds.
When choosing the size of the mattress, add to your height the length of your feet, i.e. between 21 and 34 cm.
A man or woman with a height of about 180 cm will need a bed of between 210 and 220 cm.
The minimum width for a person should be, in a double room, 90 cm, total 180 cm.
In the case of single rooms, for example singles, a minimum of 120 to 140 cm is recommended.
So that a possible visit is also comfortable.
"If not, you can apply a simple rule to calculate the width: when you lie upside down, you should have your hands comfortably shredded towards the elbows," advises the engineer Helena Prokopová, expert from Cechu čalouníkě to dekoratér, who has been dealing with the problems of healthy sleep and the ergonomics of furniture, the subject he teaches in specialized schools.
In the double rooms, each one needs its own somier and mattress, so during the purchase you have to pay attention to combining the height of the mattresses.
Otherwise, it will be necessary to mount the sockets at different heights, which is not always possible in all beds.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, models with interior docks of at least 15 cm, of which at least three centimeters are for the layer that adapts to the shapes and softens.
"When you touch it with your hand or when you settle on the mattress, you certainly shouldn't notice the docks," Helena Prokopová warns.
Each mattress requires a certain type of somier.
The fully padded bedrooms, in which the mattress and the base are like siameses, have no sense in the bedroom.
The mattresses breathe badly and you can't wash your cover, which is often done today.
And, since every night we breathe between 0,2 and 0,75 l of sweat, it is clear that after about five or seven years the mattress will begin to remind us of a large (and congested) sieve.
For this reason, the specialists reject the slogans that speak of a life of the mattress up to 25 years or even a life assurance.
However, everything has a but.
Therefore, sellers give advice: on mattresses with a width of 120 or 140 cm, carefully take care of cleaning and washing the case, but better add a mattress protector that can be removed and wash easily.
Although mattress cases with zipper closure are currently manufactured throughout their perimeter, so when they are opened they remain in two parts (something very important for washing and the size of the washing machine!), their manipulation in larger models (and for one person) by lifting the mattress may look like a fight between a fly weight and a heavy weight.
In bed, instead of a somier, do you have a firm table?
Never!
As much for beds designed to spend one night visiting.
However, you should make (if you don't already have them) ventilation holes on the table and should be used with a mattress with docks inside and a minimum height of 15 cm with the docks in bags (such as the German Taschenfederkern) and a soft layer.
Polyurethane mattresses should not be used on such bases.
For non- articulable sheet somnants containing between 14 and 18 sheets, latex mattresses or sandwich mattresses (e.g. a combination of latex and coconut fiber) may be used, although a somier with a higher number of sheets, 28 or more, in which the sheets of the lumbar area are reinforced and can be regulated.
The joint sheet somnants should not be used with a spring mattress, as they do not react to reclination.
In addition to adjusting the rigidity of the sheets, shoulder protection can also be used.
This is a special fixation of the sheets that allows you to press or even tilt the sheets in such a way that they "rode" perfectly to the shoulders during sleep.
For men who have very wide shoulders, this is something very important.
They are even remembered by mattress manufacturers who, in the "male", began to use a softer area precisely around the shoulders.
They also remember women, for whom they put a softer area around the hips.
For the most demanding customers, there are cross-structure or boards with so-called multitorsion buffering.
The pressure is distributed between different points and the tension is reduced.
You should also take into account that, even if you use the right mattress and somier, if you use a bad pillow (large and "mould"), most of the advantages will disappear.
The basic rule is simple: the pillow must hold the head and the corners can only reach the shoulders, so that the muscles of them can be relaxed.
The recommended appropriate size is 50 x 60 cm, something normal for example in Scandinavia.
When lying sideways, the pillow should be at the same level (when combined with the somier with shoulder reinforcement or the softer area of the mattress) as the height of the shoulders.
Modern mattresses have something to do, apparently, with the original mattresses filled with straw.
Manufacturers continue to use, increasingly, natural materials or, at least, mixtures.
In fact, the biological mattresses are fashionable.
Oil-based raw materials, with which polyurethane foam is manufactured, are filled with natural oils, such as rice or soybean.
In fact, virtually all known manufacturers use soya.
"Biologically, in the case of mattresses, it means that the center is manufactured only from materials of natural origin," explains Petr Vašíček of the company Tropico Plus.
Also, natural substances are used during the manufacture of mattress case, one of the first aloe vera.
But you can also opt for the microcapsules, which release a fresh aroma to forest or lavender.
There are also differences for men and women.
While men "refresh" with breeze vegetable extracts, so that the mattress fund absorbs the heat and cools the body, women prefer to "heat" the mattress.
The red pepper extract improves blood circulation, so women feel warmer.
The favorites now?
Cold foam mattresses, which are more porous, with a structure of adapted cells, make them more permeable than those of normal polyurethane and offer more permeability.
The combination of various cold and viscoelastic foam rigidities allows for the manufacture of mattresses from various areas that know perfectly where the head, shoulders and heels go.
A good quality mattress will cost you seven thousand crowns up.
Those who play a therapeutic role often have a lower VAT, as they are considered to be sanitary.
The first to gain this advantage in the Czech Republic was Gumotex.
It's complicated to save on mattresses and somnolence.
Sometimes the offers of manufacturers or vendors can be approved, which sometimes offer two mattresses for the price of one.
For example, the Magniflex brand offers Duofreeze mattresses with a foam with memory Memory attached to the case by 11.990 crowns.
The second is available free of charge.
The era of viscoelastics with an open cell structure and a high density began with Tempur's "cosmic" material.
It originally emerged as a material for NASA, because during the astronaut take-offs they were subjected to a huge overload.
Tempur softens with heat and hardens with cold.
Therefore, the warm human body exercises a perfect effect and optimally adapts its pressure.
Therefore, it is ideal to prevent sores from occurring, although also to improve comfort during sleep.
Viscoelastic foam is not only used in mattresses, but also for sanitary products, for example for pillows that are placed under the legs and relieve them, as well as their circulation.
National manufacturers, for example, use Eucatherm C or Twinsaver foam and similar.
More and more parents use people tracking devices to control their children
Fear for children leads more and more people to think of controlling them by GPS.
The system, initially designed for vehicle monitoring, can also follow the movement of people and thus contribute, for example, to the disappearance of the nine-year-old girl Anička Janatková.
At the moment the device has the approximate size of a match box, but it will soon be reduced to the size of a watch.
Many people were afraid of the missing Anička case and they began to report on the means available to protect their children better.
Even at the expense of invading your privacy.
"We all try to say that it is not about spying, but another means of reducing the chances of a tragedy," says Petr Pilin of the company Macro Weil, one of the suppliers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
"I recognize that, in certain cases, such devices can be abused, for example if they are put in someone's bag without their knowledge, but we have not yet encountered such cases."
"Most customers really buy it for security reasons," Pilin adds.
In their opinion, children should always know what the "cajita" serves and how it is used in case of emergency.
Child psychologist Dana Bočková warns about the fact that, if the child doesn't want to carry it, she'll just throw it away.
"Even the younger children show great creativity in losing certain things intentionally if they want to prevent them from being controlled."
"Before, parents had enormous confidence in mobile phones, but these could be shut down as easily as the tracking device," Bočková says.
In your opinion, it is questionable if in the event of an attack such a device is really useful.
"If this is a prepared abduction, the author will practically always check whether the child carries any kind of electronic device that can reveal his location."
"Now it's the phone."
"According to the extension of the use of tracking devices, you will also look for them, since their sale will undoubtedly be made with a lot of publicity."
"In such cases, criminals always go one step ahead of the police," the psychologist says.
However, he adds that such devices can help in the case of an improvised paedophile attack.
According to Robert Čech of the RC Monitoring company, which offers monitoring services for both vehicles and persons, even if, after an attack, the tracking device is immediately destroyed, its presence can help.
"The device can be configured to regularly send the position after a given period."
"If it is damaged, at least it will facilitate the last position of the person in question."
"The most expensive devices have an integrated inclination gauge, so if the person simply slips and stays immobile, the device will immediately issue a warning with the position in question," says Čech.
In your opinion, such a service can be obtained even with smartphones with navigation, where only a special software should be installed.
